1.00	RM_Johnson	RM Johnson	RM Johnson (born April 1, 1968) is an Essence Magazine bestselling author with nine adult urban fiction and one young adult fiction novels under his belt. He is best known for his compelling stories of love, sex, and the varies different challenges the African American community have to face. Chart topping titles like The Harris Men, The Million Dollar Divorce, Love Frustration, The Million Dollar Demise (September 2009) keeps his fans turning the page. His first non-fiction work, Why Men Fear Marriage, was released July 28, 2009.. In 2011, he released a collaborative work he did with the late E. Lynn Harris entitled, No One in the World	
